Contemporary classical music can understood belonging the period that started the mid1970s early 1990s which includes modernist postmodern neoromantic and pluralist music However the term may also employed broader sense refer all post1945 musical forms Generallyaccording whom contemporary classical music amounts the beginning the twentieth century composers classical music were experimenting with increasingly dissonant pitch language which sometimes yielded atonal pieces Following World War backlash against what they saw the increasingly exaggerated gestures and formlessness late Romanticism certain composers adopted neoclassic style which sought recapture the balanced forms and clearly perceptible thematic processes earlier styles see also New Objectivity and Social Realism After World War modernist composers sought achieve greater levels control their composition process through the use the twelve tone technique and later total serialism the same time conversely composers also experimented with means abdicating control exploring indeterminacy aleatoric processes smaller larger degrees Technological advances led the birth electronic music Experimentation with tape loops and repetitive textures contributed the advent minimalism Still other composers started exploring the theatrical potential the musical performance performance art mixed media fluxusNew works Contemporary classical music continue created Each year the Boston Conservatory Berklee presents 700 performances New works from Contemporary classical music program students comprise roughly 150 these performances some extent European and the traditions diverged after World War Among the most influential composers Europe were Pierre Boulez Luigi Nono and Karlheinz Stockhausen The first and last were both pupils Olivier Messiaen important aesthetic philosophy well group compositional techniques this time was serialism also called throughordered music total music total tone ordering which took its starting point 